caption: Had the paneer wrap and it was amazing

I have ordered chicken tikka biryani and paneer tikka curry ,look wise  its good but when we taste it its horrible in taste and in gravy tomato and onion was half cooked and its taste really bad .Never try again

Very good place to have a Indian tikka and curry.  The employees are so friendly. When I asked for chai which is not available but he specially prepared for me. We have options like bowl , wrap, salad and feast. Also some snack items and Indian sweets available I would recommend this place.
My Veggie Kofta Masala Wrap was excellent, but the side of naan was dry and too cold
Very filling. Service is consistently above par. The bill was average for the menu. They have so many reviews for a reason.
(Translated by Google) Good bhel and vada pav!  (Original) Good bhel and vada pav!
Very affordable price and decent good quantities . It was quick and nice service . Liked the food. Also it was made fresh and good quality . Quick bites or office lunch time it’s a great place.
I’d say its ok, not to spicy like authentic Indian places
Really good food. Very flavorful and delicious. Loved it!!

This place is a hidden gem! We ordered chicken biryani, lamb kofta biryani, and aloo tikka chaat - it was all so delicious and had a good spice level too! As someone who is Indian, it's hard to find a place that satisfies my pallet and this one hit the spot! I will definitely be back. I hope it doesn't close because of Covid-19.
I wish there were more places like this around town. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. Prices are reasonable I would say.
Irresponsible, they consistently advertise as open on Uber eats even when they are closed.
Normally I would have posted a pic but food looked so good I couldn't stop.
Great Chicken Tikka Masala
food was so delish. looking forward to a return trip. kinda of like a restaurant in los angeles i loved to visit.
The best indian food....
I was super full. The prices are fair for the quality of food.

Stopped there for a quick lunch as it was the only shop which was open to satisfy my Indian food craving during that time. Food was really delicious and quality was good but quantity could have been improved. You can order directly from Kiosk (perfect to avoid interaction in COVID-19 situation). Overall loved the experience.

Used the Ritual app to order takeout and was very pleased with the experience. I loved being able to choose from such a wide variety of curries for my chicken tikka masala bowl. Samosas, chutneys and naan were also tasty, and the portion was sizeable for lunch. Will definitely order from here again!
I like this venue a lot. there is a very special atmosphere. The kitcen is very tasty. the service is effective and the stuff is trained. The price is reasonable. profoundly recommend.

Went here for lunch on a recommendation from a friend.  They have great fast healthy Indian food.  First you pick your choice of a Tikka: There are 5 different choices, chicken, paneer, lamb kofta, veggie kofta and veggie. (descriptions are in my photos of the menu).  Then you select your choice of 5 different curries:  Tikka Marsala, Vindaloo, Korma, Saag, and Kadai.   (descriptions are in my photos of the menu).  Then it's your choice of a dish, either a rice bowl or feast.  My selections were a Chicken Tikka Bowl with saag curry  To drink I had a Mango Lassi that was delicious, I just wish there would've been more of it.  Tikka and Curry is a little hard to find, but well worth the trip for a delicious healthy meal.
Awful food...I luv Indian food and this place was generic.
Poor food
Had this place at my job through fooda and man did they not disappoint , I highly recommend the chicken tiki masala bowl ,its 🔥🔥🔥 , I can't wait to go to the actual restaurant one day
The food is delicious and the service is friendly & quick.  It's a great spot for a fast delicious lunch during the workweek.
Awesome food. Great price. Biryani was really good.

I was in town for a conference and happened upon this quaint place. Absolutely delicious food, their maggi is just heavenly! Reasonably priced, which is a surprise given the location. Must try if you're ever in Chicago!
You have to eat their saag lamb. Its really good. I wish I knew how they cook it. Flavor on the lamb is pretty good.
We had a superb experience at this restaurant. We liked the nice environment and the food. The waiters are super attentive. I’m glad we finally decided to visit this restaurant.
This is not at all Indian restaurant. Food taste is so worst. Not recommended
I ordered things as per menu and everything was messed up , it was delivered late as well. When I called they said the menu must be old on grub hub ... seriously ????
Fast, good prices, tasty food.  Basically like an Indian version of Chipotle.  Great lunch spot.  Pleasant atmosphere.  Only downsides are limited hours and food is not that spicy.
Some good indian food
The Mango Lassi is awesome! (The bottle on the picture is empty) The staff is friendly and the food is really good. They have have happy hours so you can get good deals in samosas and chi.

This place is absolutely one of the most pleasant place in the neighborhood. Whenever I go there I am absolutely happy. They keep their high  standard service and the topmost level of dishes  they serve. You surely will enjoy this this place. Warmly  recommended.
So delicious!! I love the chats and tikka curry combination bowls. The vada pav is just like Mumbai vada pavs 🤩

I ordered though ubereats for a few times. Great fast food style Indian food. Like the choice of rice varieties. The curry is great, but don’t ever order the naan. I am not sure if it’s because it’s for delivery or not, but they probably heated the naan in the microwave without water or a wet napkin on it. The naan is hard as a rock and not eatable. Oh, and don’t choose the More tikka n curry option either, it’s 3 dollars more and still the same amount of sauce and meat, doesn’t even cover all the rice.

Probably I had the worst biryani in my life.  Place is nice. Ppl working in here greet the customer which is only good. Over all this is not authentic Indian style. Definitely not recommend for the price. Most of the below reviews are fake paid reviews.
They cook the sauce on a pan! Love the family style

Popular Indian dishes, curries and samosas! The place feels modern and clean with an easy-to-understand menu. The options are limited, but that’s what makes it good! They already know what is tasty and they offer it in a variety: on a combo plate, wrap, or rice bowl. I believe they also have salad bowls. It doesn’t get too crowded at lunch and this is the perfect place for someone who is new to I Sian cuisine to try it out. Arguably, the tikka massala is one of the popular dishes. Highly recommended if you are looking for a place that has flavor and is different than your regular taco or sandwich. Tikka seat and eat!
Good food. Too tangy for an Indian palette
Fast service, great tasting food at a fair price. Highly recommended and don't worry they have food options to satisfy almost every dietary preference.

Ordered on Uber eats, best Indian food in entire downtown including some fast food items like Vada pav and Samosa wrap. Lived here for over 10 years but this one really made me happy, finally a place where I can keep coming back.
Nothing Indian about this place, chicken tikka tasted like water down ketchup, never had anything like it. Would not go back

Went here thinking we're getting authentic indian food, what a disappointment! Thanks but no thanks. They charged $2 for lamb kufta and only gave 2 pieces shorter than my pinkie, their sauce is basically spicy spaghetti sauce not the flavor I expected. However they earn 2 stars for fast & courteous service.
Great place for lunch. The Chicken Tikka rice bowl was delicious and is a decent size for the price.
Very good food. Loved vada paw and tika curry.
I like the mango lassi
Ordered Paneer tikka Feast, I liked it so much. Great quality, taste and service.
Paneer Tika is Awesome
Loved the spinach curry

Non spicy food. I am  a vegetarian. Even I don't take egg. This is the place in Chicago where I can get veg. Food without spicy.  They give main item in less quantity whereas the side dish on a  higher quantity. Anyway the stomach was full on that day. To be frank, still they have to improve the taste in the food. I took Veg rice with panneer gravy. Though it's named as Veg rice I could find only 4 pieces of carrot only. The size of the carrot was like a noodle piece. I am sure that they know the other vegetables like beans, cauliflower, capsicum etc. If they add more vegetables the taste of the rice will be more tasty. Its up to them to look into this.
I have ordered twice via Ritual pickup, food was good in both aspects quality and quantity, one of the best place to try Indian food in loop.
Excellent chicken tikka. Pricey, got to $15 with a side and a drink. Still would give 5 stars but they don’t recycle.
Not actually open till 8, closes at 3pm except for online delivery orders
Lots of flavor and a good value for your money. Curry's are sauteed to order, but service is quick and pleasant.
All the food tased just okay, and it wasn't authentic. But given that this isn't an Indian restaurant, rather an Indian version of Chipotle, I guess the food is as good as you would expect it to be.
Delicious Food & more choice.  Authentic TASTE. Keep it up
Loved their Bowls. Great food, fast service.
great food, hygienic and authentic taste, warm hospitality
Over all liked it. All curries tasted good but did not like the vindaloo. Good options of rice.
Average
Very pathetic don't accept card at evening no register open at evening time.dont accept cash as well.
This place is ok. The food is decent but the portions are tiny. There were only two pieces of meat in the biryani and the naan was one piece.
First time customer. A little too spice but I'll make sure to ask next time

Great lunch spot.  My colleague and I tried a rice bowl w/ paneer and a salad, along with a samosa.  Everything was fresh and delicious.  The owner was very friendly and was genuinely interested in making sure we enjoyed our experience.  He even passed around free samples of his mango lassi and chai drinks.  Highly recommended.
Best paneer Tikka I have ever had in the USA. Quality was top notch and the taste was amazing. Would recommend to anyone wanting fresh food in the Chicago area.
Delicious, will visit again
Very very less quantity for Meal Pal order.

I travel over half the year and eat chicken tikka masala everywhere I go. This was some of the best I've ever had, served up by lovely happy people who clearly enjoy cooking and serving others. It shows in the food. Mango lassi was top notch as well!
Food is great, portions are great, staff is great!  I get the chicken tikka briyani with Nan. Need to go more often!
Great flavor.   Very friendly and helpful.
Curry and naan were just not up to the mark.. dal makhni did taste good.. recommend veg options instead of non veg

Amazing place to eat fusion Indian style food. They have lots of options for vegetarian as well. Awesome concept !! Very Unique food and very tasty fresh food live on Tava. Don't miss to try Mangoo Lassi which is amazing.
Awesome place for Indian food🙏
Paneer Tikka was sour taste, had little too much tomato gravy. Their other gravy are better. I would recommend trying Samosa there too.
Very good Indian fast-food
Extremely tasty food fast!
Tirupati of Chicago.

Thank god for this place. The loop needs more good food like this. The owner was really friendly and the food was so delicious. I had the paneer feast and highly recommend it since it comes with different sides.
Yummy korma

This is a good lunch spot. I went with my boyfriend and had the Feast with chicken, vindaloo, garam masala, rice, and tomato/cucumber salad. The vindaloo was more of a tomato sauce and wasn't as spicy as I would have liked, but overall it was good. My boyfriend had the biryani bowl with lamb which I preferred, however, he didn't get the raita which would have been a nice touch. Overall good and worth another shot.

Visited yesterday for the first time and got my food to take away - LOVED every bite. Staff were friendly and helpful, space is cheery, and food is delicious. Also not sure how other reviewers were complaining about portions - I had more food than I could finish in my chicken saag rice bowl! Samosas were also fantastic. Great concept, delicious food, great experience all around. Looking forward to my next visit already.
Worst chai ever!! Ambience is good.

This is the best place to eat indian food in the loop. Menu has wide range of customizable items to choose from. Live TAVA concept is very nice. Staff is very friendly and service is fast. I would visit the place more ofteb whenever I am in the area.
Good Indian curries and snacks.
Great food. I ordered the curry bowl with biriyani rice and chicken tikka. And that was real good. I would recommend the pista lassi as well.
Finally something nearby with great taste

My new favorite lunch spot! The food is amazing with lots of choices. One of the good thing is their prices. It's reasonable, not too costly with good quantity and quality. The taste of the food is very delicious, specially their Mango Lassi.... I loved it!!! :)
Authentic Indian food served hot at a reasonable price. Liked the chipotle style of pick and choose the ingredients.

Clean and friendly place with good food! I got the 'feast' because I wanted to try multiple things. I picked the least spicy curry but it was still tasty and had a lot of flavor. Chicken tikka and naan were as great as expected. Topped off with mango lassi! I'll be going back for lunch all the time.
I believe the food is great and the staff is efficient. I would like the spicy options to be stepped up like traditional curry though. Other than that I suggest everyone to check it out!
Quick Indian food in the loop. Food is decent, but a little expensive for what you get.  Still nice to have another Indian restaurant option for lunch.
Really good Indian food!  Lots of options and super fast.  I was a huge fan of the chicken korma, tikka wraps (comes with 2 tasty sauces) and samosa.  Great spot to grab a quick flavorful lunch.

The food is great with great variety of choices in the bowl. Loved the taste of Indian Spices. Its an very nice concept of to go style, quick and easy. The place is very good, and the staff too. I would recommend it, you must try it..!!!

The quantity is not adequate in comparison with price. Food is flavorful if you get the right combination. Don't ever order lamb, they will give you meatball. I think it's alright at best but definitely won't recommend as a good value for money.
Delicious! I will definitely be back :)

So happy there's finally a quick Indian place in the loop now! It's easy to eat so I don't have to get my hands messy or spend $40 on an Indian meal. Perfect to go on during my lunch break or between my classes at DePaul. Can't wait to try some more of the menu items!!

Because of my childhood, I'm a chicken tikka masala fiend, and I get so excited whenever I see a new Indian place. Can be a bit hard to stumble upon as it's tucked into Financial Place, but I actually find the hunt charming! You're rewarded with solid curry and fairly priced for its portion size--think the curry version of Naf Naf Grill. My only complaint is the very peculiar hours, but I definitely see myself returning most often to grab samosas to snack on!
Awesome food , must visit place 👌👍

Great place for lunch quick and easy. I have catered for our company fundraiser and it was delicious , everything came out the way we had discussed. I would suggest this for lunch and dinner. My husband and I brought our infant they really accommodated our family. A lot of options for vegans, vegetarians and meat lovers.  When I order for lunch I have left overs for dinner! Great value for your money. I’m indian so I’m very picky about Indian food at restaurant and I think Tikka n Curry has really captured the authentic flavor in its dishes.
Excellent food with excellent service.. Curry and naan are best.
Pretty decent tikka masala dish. I'll 5 star it for now. Definitely worth a try
First time I had Indian food in this manner. Chipotle style Indian restaurant! Will definitely come back.

Yes! Finally somewhere I can go for lunch when near this area! Most of the other places are far, and not even worth it for the quality.  The staff is super friendly, the decorations keep the vibe alive and the small puns on the wall makes the whole experience amazing!! A great addition to the area! Much needed! 😬
The food was amazing and the service was even better. I also loved the way it was decorated. The little knick knacks on the wall made it feel very homey
Definitely my new favorite lunch spot! The menu has alot of options to choose from and the food is amazing. Great service and great restaurant!

A much needed Indian food option on this side of the Loop. Glad to see it take over the old Saucy Porka. The food is good! Selection is decent. Prices on the high end for lunch options. Given the high (and pent-up) demand, they're still working out some kinks with speeding up service. Look forward to going back regularly and getting more vegetarian options.

Overpriced and low quality food. The food barely fills half the bowl and $2 for a 1/4 of a naan is outrageous. The amount of time it takes to get through the line is way too long for this disappointment referred to as a meal. Food was not good at all. Preparing the meat and curries separately and then combining fails to impart flavor to the meat. Regardless of the preparation, the flavor of the curries were not particularly appetizing. Naan was inconsistent, some was hard and crusty others was soft and fluffy.
Amazing food, Great staff and very clean
